  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Slice the <strong>pork belly</strong> finely with a sharp knife</p><p>Rub the <strong>five-spice</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> all over the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>pork belly</strong> so that it's fully coated in spice</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced pork belly</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until it's browned</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>tamari</strong> <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>rice vinegar</strong> with 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> braising liquid</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>star anise</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>to the <strong>pork belly</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Add the <strong>braising liquid</strong> and bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 40-45 min or until the pork belly is tender</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pork belly is cooking, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Crush the <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> (keep them in the bag so you don't lose them!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1165.step-4.new-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
